{
  "text": "Data analysis. The reconstruction scheme is based on the Hybrid-Input-Output (HIO) algorithm [CITATION_1] 31 , making use of the additional knowledge of the complex-valued illumination function P(r) characterized by ptychography in an antecedent experiment [CITATION_2] 32 . The knowledge of P(r) is necessary to disentangle contrast introduced by the sample from wave-field structures already present in the incoming x-ray beam. Like computational spectacles, it corrects the spherical aberration of the Be CRLs. As described in the previous section, the conical imaging geometry is equivalent to a parallel-beam geometry with a propagation distance of z eff = z d /M = 112 mm between object and detector plane.",
  "citation_candidates": [
